# Trading Journal — scheduled jobs (supercronic format: standard cron, 5 fields).
#
# Each job's output goes to the container's stdout/stderr, visible in Railway logs.
# The actual interval applied by a job is typically governed by an env var
# (e.g. BROKER_SYNC_INTERVAL_MINUTES): supercronic only controls how often the
# script runs, the script decides which work is actually due.
#
# To add a new scheduled job: append a line below. Commit the change → next
# deploy of the `scheduler` service picks it up.

# Broker auto-sync — runs every 5 min; the script picks only connections
# whose last_sync_at is older than BROKER_SYNC_INTERVAL_MINUTES (default 15).
*/5 * * * * php /var/www/api/cli/sync-brokers.php
